OL,13,FHere's how science normally works.
OL,14,FYou do a study. You submit a paper
OL,15,Fdescribing that study to a scientific
OL,16,Fjournal. The editor of the journal
OL,17,Fchooses to reject it outright, or
OL,18,Fsend it to peer-review. The peer-
OL,19,Freviewers give their opinion, and
OL,20,Fsome (hopefully) constructive
OL,21,Fcomments.
OL,3,CPublishing scientific papers without
OL,4,Cpeer review has advantages - but
OL,5,Cdangers too
